      "timestep_posted": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, a pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering. This specimen retains its original 13B-REW twin-rotor powerplant, delivering seamless boost through its factory sequential twin-turbocharger system. The vacuum control network has been meticulously validated to ensure a flawless transition at 4,500 RPM. The chassis features the original double-wishbone suspension architecture with all bushings and dampers in factory-spec condition, maintaining the legendary 50/50 weight distribution and telepathic steering response. Power is delivered through a precise five-speed manual gearbox to a Torsen limited-slip differential that remains tight and responsive. The exterior retains its original high-gloss finish with consistent paint depth across all aluminum and steel panels, while the interior is free of the common heat-related plastics degradation. Recent compression testing shows robust, uniform pulses across all rotor faces, confirming the health of the apex seals. A rare opportunity for the discerning collector to acquire a mechanically unmolested rotary icon in its purest form.",
      "price": 48500.0,
